text: Louňovice pod Blaníkem () is a town in Benešov District, the Czech Republic. Around 700 people live there. ==Notable people== *Jan Dismas Zelenka (1679–1745), Baroque composer and musician *Petr Borkovec (born 1970), poet, translator and journalist ==References== Category:Towns in the Czech Republic
title: Louňovice pod Blaníkem
